<p>The television show <i><b><a href="/wiki/Lost_(TV_series)" title="Lost (TV series)">Lost</a></b></i> includes a number of mysterious elements that have been ascribed to <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> or <a href="/wiki/Supernatural" title="Supernatural">supernatural</a> phenomena, usually concerning <a href="/wiki/Coincidences" title="Coincidences" class="mw-redirect">coincidences</a>, <a href="/wiki/Synchronicity" title="Synchronicity">synchronicity</a>, <a href="/wiki/D%C3%A9j%C3%A0_vu" title="Déjà vu">déjà vu</a>, temporal and <a href="/wiki/Spatial_anomaly" title="Spatial anomaly" class="mw-redirect">spatial anomalies</a>, <a href="/wiki/Paradox" title="Paradox">paradoxes</a>, and other puzzling phenomena. The creators of the series refer to these as part of the <a href="/wiki/Mythology" title="Mythology">mythology</a> of the series.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
